This is a known breaking change. Android 15 (API 35) enforces **edge-to-edge** rendering, which means `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` is ignored. .NET 10 MAUI targets API 35 by default.

**The fix:** Use the `WindowInsets` API to react to the keyboard (IME) appearing. In your `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
using Android.OS;
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        var rootView = Window!.DecorView.FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;

        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(rootView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }

    private class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

            // Use the larger of IME or nav bar bottom inset
            int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);
            v.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottom);

            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

**What this does:**
- Listens for inset changes (keyboard open/close)
- Adjusts the root view's bottom padding to match the keyboard height
- Falls back to navigation bar inset when the keyboard is closed

**Also ensure** your `AndroidManifest.xml` has `adjustResize` on the activity (it still helps the insets system report correctly):

```xml
<activity android:windowSoftInputMode="adjustResize" ... />
```

This replaces the old `Platform.CurrentActivity.Window.SetSoftInputMode(...)` pattern entirely.
